---
description: "Logging and error handling"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Logging

- Use ILogger
- Log:
  - Errors
  - Important business actions

# Error Handling
- Use global exception middleware
- Do not try/catch everywhere

# Security
- Do not log sensitive data

# Example
_logger.LogError(ex, "Error processing payment for UserId={UserId}", userId);